<p>Grantee agrees and consents to the conditions of the proposal submitted to the Energy Foundation and to the following conditions of the grant:</p>

<p>Grantee shall use this grant solely for the purposes as expressed in <%=fluxx_request.fiscal_or_program_possessive%> <%=ga_proposal_and_budget_date%> to the Energy Foundation.  It is understood that these grant funds will be used for such purposes substantially in accordance with the budget submitted.  Grantee shall repay to the Energy Foundation any portion of the amount granted which is not used for the purposes of this grant.</p>

<p>Grantee ensures that the grant funds under this award will be used in compliance with all applicable anti-terrorist financing and asset control laws, regulations, rules and executive orders.  Grantee also agrees to take all reasonable precautions to ensure that any person or group expected to receive money from the grantee will neither make any payment nor provide any material support to any person on any United States government list of suspected terrorists.</p>

<p>The grantee agrees that no funds provided pursuant to this Grant Agreement may be used to contact, or urge the public to contact, members of a legislative body for the purpose of proposing, supporting, or opposing legislation; or to advocate the adoption or rejection of legislation.  See Treasury Regulation section 1.501(c)(3)-1(c)(3)(ii).</p>

<p class='page-break'>The interim reports should set forth (a) a brief description of progress to date toward completing the work described in the proposal, and (b) how the proceeds of the grant have been spent to date i.e., a financial report showing actual expenditures according to the budget categories as originally proposed.</p>

<p>Final reports, both narrative and financial, shall be due no later than two months after the termination of the grant period. The interim and final financial reports should show revenues and expenses for both this grant and the project. Clearly show the amount funded by the Energy Foundation and how these funds have been spent according to the categories of the submitted budget. Use three columns for the report:</p>

<table>
<tr><td width='40'></td><td width='75' valign="top">Column 1 -</td><td valign="top">Present the entire project budget (all sources of revenue and expenditures) as included in the original proposal;</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td valign="top">Column 2 -</td><td valign="top">Present the actual revenue and expenditures for the project in total;</td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td valign="top">Column 3 -</td><td valign="top">Present the actual revenue and expenditures funded by the Energy Foundation grant only.</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Reports are due as follows:</p>

<table>
<tr height=1><td width='40' valign="top"></td><td width='320' valign="top"></td><td></td></tr>
<%= report_details %>
</table>


