<p>Successive payments after the initial payment(s) described above are contingent upon Energy Foundation staff review of performance and receipt of the progress reports.</p>

<p>If grantee intends to apply for a renewal grant, the Energy Foundation must receive an interim narrative and financial report along with the new grant application no later than two months before the Energy Foundation board meeting.  The board meets in early March, late June, and early November.</p>

<p>Grantee shall not use any portion of the funds granted to carry on propaganda or otherwise to attempt to influence specific legislation, either by direct or grassroots lobbying, to influence the outcome of any specific voter registration drive, to make grants to individuals on a non-objective basis, nor for any non-charitable or non-educational purpose.  Please include a positive disclaimer to both narrative and financial reports that no Energy Foundation funds were used for lobbying purposes.</p>

<p>Grantee shall notify the Energy Foundation of any organizational changes during the term of the grant, including, but not limited to, changes in key personnel, changes in tax status, and changes in the project timing or goals.</p>

<p>Grantee shall permit representatives of the Energy Foundation to visit the premises and review the activities of the Grantee with respect to the programs supported by this grant.</p>

<p>Grantee may announce receipt of this grant.  Please furnish the Energy Foundation with any results of this announcement.</p>

<p class='page-break'>Please refer to grant number <b><%= fluxx_request.grant_id %></b> in all future correspondence and reports which relate to this grant.</p>

<p>The board and staff of the Energy Foundation are pleased to be able to make this grant to your organization.  Please sign and return one copy of this grant agreement as evidence of your understanding and agreement with the terms and conditions defined in this letter.</p>


